radiographic_examinations.findings: Bibasilar atelectasis is mild and symmetric. The liver is homogeneous in attenuation without focal hepatic lesion identified. The gallbladder is surgically absent. The appendix is dilated at its mid portion to the tip measuring up to 10 mm in diameter with hyperemia, surrounding soft tissue stranding and trace fluid. The bladder is moderately well distended and grossly unremarkable. Pelvic free fluid is trace.
